{
  "text": "SNAP-25 belongs to the SNARE superfamily of membrane proteins that participate in synaptic vesicle (SV) exocytosis. It contributes two alpha-helices in the formation of the exocytotic fusion complex together with syntaxin-1 and synaptobrevin/VAMP [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Besides acting as a fundamental component of the SNARE complex, SNAP-25 has been shown to negatively modulate voltage gated calcium channels in various overexpression systems [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] and in cultured hippocampal neurons [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] .",
  "correct_citation": {
